{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:job.10",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 10",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 10 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:1",
      "text": "Weary in my soul, I will pour my words with groans upon him: I will speak being straitened in the bitterness of my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:2",
      "text": "And I will say to the Lord, Do not teach me to be impious; and wherefore hast thou thus judged me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:3",
      "text": "Is it good before thee if I be unrighteous? for thou hast disowned the work of thy hands, and attended to the counsel of the ungodly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:4",
      "text": "Or dost thou see as a mortal sees? or wilt thou look as a man sees?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:5",
      "text": "Or is thy life human, or thy years the years of a man,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:6",
      "text": "that thou hast enquired into mine iniquity, and searched out my sins?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:7",
      "text": "For thou knowest that I have not committed iniquity: but who is he that can deliver out of thy hands?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:8",
      "text": "Thy hands have formed me and made me; afterwards thou didst change thy mind, and smite me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:9",
      "text": "Remember that thou hast made me as clay, and thou dost turn me again to earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:10",
      "text": "Hast thou not poured me out like milk, and curdled me like cheese?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:11",
      "text": "And thou didst clothe me with skin and flesh, and frame me with bones and sinews.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:12",
      "text": "And thou didst bestow upon me life and mercy, and thy oversight has preserved my spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:13",
      "text": "Having these things in thyself, I know that thou canst do all things; for nothing is impossible with thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:14",
      "text": "And if I should sin, thou watchest me; and thou hast not cleared me from iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:15",
      "text": "Or if I should be ungodly, woe is me: and if I should be righteous, I cannot lift myself up, for I am full of dishonour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:16",
      "text": "For I am hunted like a lion for slaughter; for again thou hast changed and art terribly destroying me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:17",
      "text": "renewing against me my torture: and thou hast dealt with me in great anger, and thou hast brought trials upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:18",
      "text": "Why then didst thou bring me out of the womb? and why did I not die, and no eye see me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:19",
      "text": "and I become as if I had not been? for why was I not carried from the womb to the grave?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:20",
      "text": "Is not the time of my life short? suffer me to rest a little,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:21",
      "text": "before I go whence I shall not return, to a land of darkness and gloominess;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.10.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:22",
      "text": "to a land of perpetual darkness, where there is no light, neither can any one see the life of mortals.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
